    "client_msg_id": "280ac6c7-ff15-45fa-8355-7dd5a9900326",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "On <http://vitor.io/on-dynamicland>\n\nThere seem to be three distinct goals that tend to get conflated:\n\n1. Seeing as you create.\n2. Seeing what others have created. Or rather, creating in a way that makes creations easy for others to appreciate/remix/contribute to.\n3. Keeping a closely-coupled group on a single page about what they are seeing.\n\nAll three directions seem complementary, in that there's no reason they can't steal ideas from each other. The eventual goal seems like a workspace that supports groups spanning a spectrum of sizes (including individuals), and that is easy to export from one group to another.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1554146676.000300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
